<subSubSection id="CF0C86A9F06695128F26D95C9DD079BB" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="FB2CC1779C737D54C90689A6779DCB33" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C08D58BBAB2309AB7C9DA94A02D3D2D6" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName id="0319BCE22B899EFD524AAE7AE74F1C6F" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aragonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aragonia">Zygaena rhadamanthus aragonia</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the Spanish provinces of Cuenca and Teruel. While it is reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="BAE447D047107FE7089FA15C3A102FB3" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</taxonomicName>
from south-eastern and southern-central France, the placement of this taxon as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="EDA78C06EB9851E6F30A48CAAACA9425" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1406C46207655A58CBE1B65B66F46490" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98), which he reinstated as a valid subspecies, is inconsistent with the geographical distribution, its 
<normalizedToken id="CACB9F1E78C00EA321C0A43AF517D691" originalValue="‘griseoid’">'griseoid'</normalizedToken>
phenotype and the presence of a strong abdominal cingulum. As a consequence, 
<taxonomicName id="4471EE15A48DBA02B32B953C9BBCB93A" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aragonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aragonia">Zygaena rhadamanthus aragonia</taxonomicName>
is here reinstated (stat. rev.) as a valid subspecies (
<bibRefCitation id="45C4E6038E58CDBF0676415B8FBE6C25" author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan 1996</bibRefCitation>
: 130). It should be noted that 
<taxonomicName id="C9A270E26D3D23FF8A258E3970140FED" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">Zygaena rhadamanthus aurargentea</taxonomicName>
also has a griseoid phenotype and a strong abdominal cingulum, but the two taxa are geographically separated by a large lowland area that includes the River Ebro.
</paragraph>
